commit.message: Add lock when compiling jq programs

Pass -lm to compiler when building extension

This attempts to address the manylinux wheels not working on some
distributions such as Ubuntu 16.04 due to the removal of the symbol
scalbln ( double x, int n ) @@ GLIBC_2.2.5

Original user report: https://github.com/mwilliamson/jq.py/issues/43

Further discussion: https://github.com/joerick/cibuildwheel/issues/343
Update development status classifier to Production/Stable
Generate jq.c using CIBW_BEFORE_BUILD when building wheels
Build oniguruma and jq in _deps directory
Add leading underscores to private module members
Allow retrieval of original program string
